fix(vendor): update 'zlib' to 1.2.12+
The 'develop' branch has a few additional regressions fixed.

tweak(graphics/five): remove `boost_filesystem` dep
This is unneeded and it propagated fairly far down the line.

tweak(graphics/five): refactor graphics proxy dll loading
As seen in a forum topic (https://forum.cfx.re/t/4850555), old ReShade named `d3d9.dll` still prevents the game from loading.
Instead, we'll *always* load system DLLs in the main launcher, and move the viability check logic to rage:graphics:five, which has also been cleaned up a little.
This has been tested with: - This ancient '0.18.7' ReShade as `d3d9.dll` (blocked, correctly) - ReShade '5.1.0' as `d3d9.dll` (working) - ENBSeries '0.3.8.7' as `d3d11.dll` (working)

Revert "tweak(client/core): nvidia, fuck you."
The gift that keeps on giving: NVIDIA drivers. Some users seem to crash in new places with `disable.txt` present and used.
Seriously?!
This reverts commit 02df4a52b1dba9b56a89b10bf59be7c9ff79c0d9.

tweak(client/core): nvidia, fuck you.
Apparently ba693365d151cb3d61e1fd1bc08f9f65f66d13ae wasn't enough to fix the .toc corruption from nvPSShaderDiskCache.cpp/the NvShaderDiskCache perf strategy.
Instead, this change just disables the shader cache entirely. Using a hacky way.

tweak(common): json.hpp->rapidjson for Error.cpp
rapidjson is a little smaller codegen-wise, and Error.cpp is included all over the place on client.

tweak(resources): no glm binding for metadata loader
This inflates binary size by about 1MB for an API that isn't usually exposed, needed, or used.
tweak(ext/cfx-ui): server not cached if it's not the right game
fix(ext/cfx-ui): was adding servers that aren't the right game

tweak(ci): rework .gitlab-ci.yml
This also adds an upload_review task for RDR, but that's ~unrelated.

fix(scripting/v8): amend argument count check for invokeNative
This seems to be the underlying issue for the dump reported and sent in https://forum.cfx.re/t/4845612 - a `Citizen.invokeNativeByHash(1)` call.

fix(level-loader/five): re-add reloading on mode switch
This issue was introduced in 83051726e61a5c7ff33d999317b67179155c8fba, likely inadvertently.
Reported in https://forum.cfx.re/t/4845352.
